CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 21, 1958, pg. 10, reads: "Planning a Career - Seventeen - year - old Stanford Eddins, a June graduate, confers with Urban League guidance specialist Florene A. Cherry. Stanford, who plans a career in science, will enroll at Howard University next fall."
TitMainTitle: Stanford Eddins and Urban League guidance specialist Florene A. Cherry standing on either side of Urban League's "Tomorrow's Scientists and Technicians" careers poster
